<h5>Creating a PDF File</h5>

<p>A <strong>PDF File</strong> (Portable Document Format) can be read by anyone with AdobeÆ; AcrobatÆ; Reader&#x2122;, a free program that can be easily downloaded from the Internet.</p>

<p>Adobe&reg; Acrobat&reg; is the original program that allows you to create and work with PDF files. Because PDF format has become so popular, many programs have incorporated the ability to Save As or Publish a document in pdf file format. If that option is not available in the program you are using, you can either purchase or download a free program that converts your printout to pdf format. Because there are many options, explore and learn about the options you have to create pdf files.</p> 

<p>For newer versions of the Microsoft suite of software programs, the easiest option is to select Save As or Publish when saving the document and then choose PDF as the file type.</p>

